            {
              "id": "04c35e3a-698d-3dfd-bea8-e4eac9302903",
              "name": "HTTP Client Directly Receives Stack Trace or Debug Trace String from Controller",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"HTTP Client Directly Receives Stack Trace or Debug Trace String from Controller\" is a vulnerability that occurs when an application inadvertently discloses sensitive information such as stack traces or debug traces to the client. This can happen when an exception is thrown in a Java application and the stack trace is sent back to the client in the HTTP response. This information can be used by an attacker to gain insights into the internal workings of the application, which can be exploited to launch further attacks.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to catch exceptions and handle them appropriately, without revealing any sensitive information to the client. This can be achieved by implementing a global exception handler that catches all exceptions and returns a generic error message to the client.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is an example of how to implement a global exception handler in a Spring Boot application:\n\n```java\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.ControllerAdvice;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.ExceptionHandler;\n\n@ControllerAdvice\npublic class GlobalExceptionHandler {\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(Exception.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<String> handleException(Exception e) {\n        return new ResponseEntity<>(\"An error occurred. Please try again later.\", HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIn this example, any exception that is thrown in the application will be caught by the `handleException` method, which returns a generic error message to the client.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe above code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- Spring Boot Starter Web\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 2017: A3-Sensitive Data Exposure](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A3_2017-Sensitive_Data_Exposure)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-209: Information Exposure Through an Error Message](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/209.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-209",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/209.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-209"
                ]
              }
