            {
              "id": "1d588413-3ab5-3c91-8e88-abbec1ceb759",
              "name": "Server-Side URL Fetch Vulnerability with User-Controlled Parameter",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Server-Side URL Fetch Vulnerability with User-Controlled Parameter\" is a security vulnerability that occurs when an application fetches a URL from a server-side resource using a user-controlled parameter. This can lead to various security issues such as Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF), where an attacker can make requests to internal resources behind the firewall, which are not directly accessible by the attacker.\n\nIn Java, this vulnerability can occur when using the `URL` class to open a stream to a user-controlled URL.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to validate and sanitize user input. Avoid using user-controlled data to form a URL without proper validation and sanitization. If possible, use a fixed URL or a URL from a trusted source.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a simple fix for the vulnerability:\n\n```java\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.MalformedURLException;\n\npublic class Main {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        String url = getUserInput();\n\n        // Validate the URL\n        if (!isValidURL(url)) {\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid URL\");\n        }\n\n        try (InputStream in = new URL(url).openStream()) {\n            // ...\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            // Handle exception\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static String getUserInput() {\n        // Get user input\n        return \"\";\n    }\n\n    private static boolean isValidURL(String url) {\n        try {\n            new URL(url);\n            return true;\n        } catch (MalformedURLException e) {\n            return false;\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIn this code, the `isValidURL` method is used to validate the user-controlled URL before opening a stream to it.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example does not require any additional library dependencies.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Resources\n\n- [OWASP Server-Side Request Forgery Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Server_Side_Request_Forgery_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-918: Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/918.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-918",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/918.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "8.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-918"
                ]
              }
