            {
              "id": "2000f219-514b-3dfe-a1d4-186b7a76396c",
              "name": "Double-Encoding Host Confusion Vulnerability in Redirect Validation",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Double-Encoding Host Confusion Vulnerability in Redirect Validation\" is a security vulnerability in Java programming language that occurs when an application decodes user input twice. This can lead to a situation where an attacker can bypass security checks by double-encoding a malicious URL. The application's first decode operation decodes the URL into a seemingly harmless form that passes the security checks. However, a second decode operation (which might be performed by a downstream component) can transform the URL back into a malicious form.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, the application should avoid double-decoding user input. If the application needs to decode user input, it should do so only once, and it should perform all necessary security checks after decoding. The application should also validate the host of the URL to ensure it is a trusted host before redirecting.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\n```java\n@RestController\n@AssignmentHints({\"openredirect.hint7\", \"openredirect.hint8\"})\npublic class OpenRedirectTask4 implements AssignmentEndpoint {\n\n  private static final Set<String> INTERNAL_HOSTS = Set.of(\"webgoat.local\", \"localhost\", \"127.0.0.1\");\n\n  @PostMapping(\"/OpenRedirect/task4\")\n  @ResponseBody\n  public AttackResult doubleDecode(@RequestParam(\"target\") String target) {\n    if (target == null || target.isBlank()) {\n      return failed(this).feedback(\"openredirect.failure4\").output(\"Empty value\").build();\n    }\n\n    // Only decode once\n    String decoded = URLDecoder.decode(target, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n    String lower = decoded.toLowerCase();\n    boolean appearsInternal =\n        lower.startsWith(\"https://webgoat.local\") || lower.startsWith(\"http://webgoat.local\");\n\n    URI uri;\n    try {\n      uri = new URI(decoded);\n    } catch (URISyntaxException e) {\n      return failed(this).feedback(\"openredirect.failure4\").output(\"Invalid URL\").build();\n    }\n\n    String host = uri.getHost();\n\n    // Validate the host\n    if (!INTERNAL_HOSTS.contains(host)) {\n      return failed(this).feedback(\"openredirect.failure4\").output(\"Invalid host\").build();\n    }\n\n    // Continue with the rest of the code...\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- Spring Web (`spring-web`)\n- Spring Boot Starter Web (`spring-boot-starter-web`)\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Unvalidated Redirects and Forwards Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Unvalidated_Redirects_and_Forwards_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-601: URL Redirection to Untrusted Site ('Open Redirect')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/601.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-601",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/601.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "8.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-601"
                ]
              }
