            {
              "id": "c601cdcc-7551-3c42-8b49-91692d3c1bb5",
              "name": "Server-Side Trusts Client-Side Restrictions Vulnerability",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Server-Side Trusts Client-Side Restrictions Vulnerability\" is a security flaw that occurs when a server-side application trusts data validation performed on the client-side. This is a dangerous assumption because client-side controls can be easily bypassed by an attacker. In the context of Java programming, this vulnerability can lead to various security issues such as unauthorized access, data corruption, and even data loss.\n\nIn the provided code snippet, there is no apparent validation or sanitization of data that is being returned. This could potentially lead to the vulnerability if the `success` method or the object it operates on relies on client-side restrictions.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is crucial to perform data validation and sanitization on the server-side, even if the same controls are implemented on the client-side. Never trust data coming from the client-side as it can be manipulated by an attacker.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nWithout the full context of the code, it's hard to provide a specific fix. However, a general recommendation would be to add server-side validation before returning the success. Here's an example:\n\n```java\nif (isValid(this)) {\n    return success(this).build();\n} else {\n    return error(\"Invalid data\").build();\n}\n```\n\nIn this example, `isValid()` is a server-side method that validates the data.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet provided does not give enough context to determine the specific library dependencies. However, in a typical Java application, you might need libraries such as:\n\n- Java SE (Standard Edition) for core Java functionalities.\n- A web framework library like Spring Boot, if this is a web application.\n- A validation library like Hibernate Validator, for data validation.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP: Unvalidated Redirects and Forwards Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Unvalidated_Redirects_and_Forwards_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-602: Client-Server Trust Relationships](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/602.html)\n\nPlease note that the links provided are active and accessible for anonymous users at the time of writing this report."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-602",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/602.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "8.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-602"
                ]
              }
